    <text id="B1251T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Tukey's telegram informs Brown that he has an urgent need to travel to
                Richmond.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    The Western Union Telegraph Company.
                </head>

               

                <p>Dated, <hi rend="underline">Staunton, <abbr expan="March">Mch</abbr> 15</hi> 1867</p>

                <p>Received at <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="Richmond">Richd</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="March">"</abbr> 15</hi></p>

                <p>To <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="Brigadier General">Brig Genl</abbr> O
                    Brown</hi></p>

                <p>I desire to visit Richmond on urgent private business cannot wait to communicate
                    through the ordinary channel can I come please answer tonight.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>F.S. Tukey<lb/>Asst Supt<lb/>B. R. F. &amp; A. L.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
